laboratory_examinations.findings: Hyperintense signal image in the spinal cord from T6 to T11 levels in T2 and STIR sequences, occupying more than 80% of the circumference of the spinal cord. Consistent with cytotoxic edema or myelomalacia. Enlarged perimedullary vessels in the posterior epidural region with hyperintense signal voids in T1 and hypointense signal in T2 sequences.

Right perimedullary fistula type I, with a feeding artery of the radiculopial branch and a perimedullary venous drainage of the segmental artery of the right L2. The fistula was satisfactorily embolized with a 20% histoacryl-lipiodol emulsion.
